5. Default and static Methods (Interface Enhancement) - Interfaces can have method body
     Why : Backward compatibility and Enable functional programming support
      If you add a method to interface → all classes break so Java 8 introduced:
      ✅ default methods - ✔ Allows adding new methods without breaking existing code
      ✅ static methods - ✔ Called using: MyInterface.display();
      interface MyInterface {
          default void show() {
              System.out.println("Default method");
          }
      }
      interface MyInterface {
          static void display() {
              System.out.println("Static method");
          }
 6. Method References - Shortcut for lambda
   Types:
    Static Method Reference - Class::staticMethod, list.stream().map(Math::sqrt);
    Instance Method Reference (Object)-  object::instanceMethod , System.out::println
    Instance Method Reference (Class) - ClassName::instanceMethod , list.stream().map(String::toUpperCase);
    Constructor Reference -  Class::new, Supplier<List<String>> s = ArrayList::new;

7. Optional Class - Avoids NullPointerException
              Avoid get() without check ,  Use map() + orElse() 
              Don’t use Optional in fields (bad practice)
    Optional<String> opt = Optional.of("Hello");
    Optional<String> opt2 = Optional.ofNullable(null);
    Optional<String> opt3 = Optional.empty();

✔ isPresent() -opt.isPresent();
✔ ifPresent() - opt.ifPresent(x -> System.out.println(x));
✔ get() ⚠️ risky - opt.get();
✔ orElse() -opt.orElse("Default");
✔ orElseGet() - opt.orElseGet(() -> "Generated");
✔ orElseThrow() - opt.orElseThrow(() -> new RuntimeException());
✔ map() - opt.map(String::length);

Optional<User> user = repo.findById(id);
